{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"326393f9-6728-42e0-a6f5-1350dcde28e0","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to **MSTest v3**:\n\n### 1. `.csproj` changes\n- **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n- **Add** the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (replaces both the framework and adapter)\n- **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove this -->\n<Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n\n<!-- Add this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n\n<!-- Update this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.12.0\" />\n```\n\n### 2. Source code\nYour `using` statements and attributes (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, `Assert.*`) are **already compatible** — no code changes needed. MSTest v3 keeps the same `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace.\n\n### Optional but recommended\n- Upgrade `<TargetFramework>` from `net462` to `net8.0` or `net9.0` if possible.\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dccf658a-58b0-492b-905e-98969cf9a563","outputTokens":319},"id":"b45c2f0d-079f-4411-a3ab-67bd74bdf0b2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:55:44.288Z","parentId":"4fab41c1-7f6a-4167-82be-91312913400e"}
